  "url": "https://www.tamilmirror.lk/\u0b9a\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd/\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc8-\u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95-\u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1/175-303450",
  "time_ut": 1662106469,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bae\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Duty cannot be shirked",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Karu Jayasuriya, President of the National Movement for Social Justice, has said that the entire country has a duty to find solutions to the massive economic and political crises that Sri Lanka is currently facing, and it cannot be avoided.",
        "Legislators should act as pioneers in fulfilling this duty. And other trade unions of the country, scholars and society should accept this responsibility and work. We are constantly emphasizing this. He also said that we consider it a positive thing that many trade union organizations and the government of the country are paying major attention to this issue.",
        "The basic issues for this should be done by the Parliament of the country. For that short term, medium term and long term work plans should be formulated and implemented. And to create the necessary public acceptance and transparency for political and economic reforms, identified reforms should be implemented immediately.",
        "Repealing the 20th Constitutional Amendment and passing it would remove the vested powers. For that, the highlights of the 19th constitutional amendment should be re-implemented. We have stressed the importance of this to the President and the Minister of Justice on several occasions. We appreciate that the government is paying attention in this regard.",
        "After conveying the High Court recommendations regarding the 22nd Constitutional Amendment to the Speaker, we expect it to be submitted to the Parliament soon and passed. Similarly, we request all the members of parliament to work together for the future of the future generations of this country. He said that in this regard, we emphasize that the political parties and parliamentarians of the country will be evaluated based on the way they work in the future."
      ],
